main event: A chrome sphere-shaped object was sighted over Davenport, Iowa on April 12, 1965.
interesting points: The object was round and silver in color, observed for about 5 seconds as it went over a Second Street tower near the Inland Aerial Bridge.
The object then disappeared from view.
The object appeared to be approximately 6 feet in diameter.
Photographs of the object were taken, but the photographs were determined to show a 'chemical mess' rather than the actual object.
The report was filed as a 'sighting' with 'no case, object not seen'.
photographs: yes, but determined to be of poor quality
